CAPE TOWN - The Western Cape legislature will debate Premier Helen Zille's controversial tweets defending colonialism. Zille s comments were widely criticised on social media, with many slamming them as being offensive.READ: Zille to learn fate on SundayThe premier later apologised after taking flak from politicians and the public.The ANC, which is on the opposition benches in the province, called for a Debate of Provincial Importance, saying Zille must explain her views.On 2 April, the DA Federal Executive Committee will meet to determine a way forward.eNCA